700437f-a.title: Bronx: Astor Avenue - Matthews Avenue
700437f-a.text:
Astor Avenue, north side, between Matthews and Hronxwood
Avenues, showing an old barn, now used as a place fror which
locally-grown vegetables are sold. This was formerly part of
the Wm. W. Astor property. On the south side of the avenue
can be seen cultivated land. In the background apoears Public
School lo. 8i, at Golden and aace Avenues, and on the extreme
rioht appears, under construction, part of Christopher Wolumbus
Himu School.
April 3, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
One of the smaller barns, seen from Bronxwood Avenue.
April 3, 1938
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUTIONS
